  "notes": {
    "tripleVsCombined": "Triple Biology includes all Combined Science content plus additional higher-tier topics and more depth. Topics unique to Triple or significantly expanded include: culturing microorganisms, cell specialisation detail, monoclonal antibodies, the brain, the eye, sex-linked inheritance, trophic levels and biomass transfer, plant diseases.",
    "requiredPracticals": "AQA has 10 required practicals: microscopy, osmosis, food tests, enzymes, photosynthesis, reaction time, decay, field investigations, plant hormones, and microorganism growth.",
    "mathsSkills": "Biology requires maths skills including: calculating magnification, percentage change, mean/median/mode, interpreting graphs, using standard form, calculating cross-sectional areas of zones of inhibition, probability in genetics (Punnett squares).",
    "workingScientifically": "All exam boards assess Working Scientifically: experimental design, variables, risk assessment, data analysis, evaluating methods, drawing conclusions, identifying sources of error."
  }
